    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meal 1: </strong>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat and once hot, add your <strong>chicken </strong>to the dish and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to brown</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-chicken-tagine-x-spiced-chicken-and-chickpea-flatbreads/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and cut your<strong> brown onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> and cut into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p><p>Add the <strong>onion wedges, chopped pepper</strong> and <strong>crushed garlic</strong> to the dish with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-chicken-tagine-x-spiced-chicken-and-chickpea-flatbreads/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>ras el hanout </strong>and<strong> ground turmeric </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 550ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [700ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[930ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> with your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>sultanas</strong> then bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, put the dish in the oven and cook, covered, for 45 min<strong> </strong>or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken & sultana tagine</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-chicken-tagine-x-spiced-chicken-and-chickpea-flatbreads/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>When everything's nearly ready, reboil half a kettle and heat a small dry pan over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> flaked almonds </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Add your <strong>couscous</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a heatproof bowl with 130ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [190ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [260ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, cover and set aside until all of the liquid has been absorbed</p><p>Fluff with a fork before serving and stir through the <strong>toasted almonds</strong> with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>almond couscous</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-chicken-tagine-x-spiced-chicken-and-chickpea-flatbreads/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chicken & sultana tagine </strong>and most of the sauce (you'll eat the rest tomorrow!) with the<strong> almond couscous </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p><p>Pull the<strong> remaining chicken & sultana tagine </strong>using 2 forks and give everything a good mix up, then cool down quickly (within 2 hours max) and refrigerate in a covered container. Enjoy within 24 hours</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-chicken-tagine-x-spiced-chicken-and-chickpea-flatbreads/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meal 2: </strong>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Transfer the <strong>pulled chicken & sultana tagine </strong>to a pot with your<strong> chickpeas</strong> (no need to drain!) with all the<strong> bean water</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[85ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook over a medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, for 10-12 min or until the chickpeas have softened and it is piping hot throughout \u2013 this is your <strong>pulled chicken & sultana tagine with chickpeas</strong></p><p>You can only reheat your food once, then enjoy straight away</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-chicken-tagine-x-spiced-chicken-and-chickpea-flatbreads/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>When everything's nearly ready, add your <strong>naan[s]</strong> to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 3 min or until the bread is hot</p><p>Combine your <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>mayo</strong> in a small bowl with a small splash of <strong>cold water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>harissa mayo</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-chicken-tagine-x-spiced-chicken-and-chickpea-flatbreads/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> pulled chicken & sultana tagine with chickpeas </strong>over the<strong> warmed naan</strong></p><p>Drizzle the<strong> harissa mayo </strong>over the top and sprinkle over the <strong>chopped spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
